GLADAFRICA Championship side TS Sporting has confirmed Benson Mhlongo as the club coach. Mhlongo, a former Orlando Pirates player and Diski Challenge team coach, become Sporting third coach since the beginning of the season. He will be taking over from goalkeeper coach Tendai Tanyanyiwa who took over from Milton Dlamini, who left the club in December, having joined them at the beginning of the season. Mhlongo is returning to familiar territory as he was in charge of the team from July 2018 until November of the same year. The club confirmed his appointment in a brief statement released on Wednesday. “TS Sporting Football Club is proud to announce with immediate effect the return of Benson Mhlongo as head coach,” the statement said. Mhlogo was last at Black Leopards as assistant to Floyd Mogale but departed near the end of 2021. 